UPDATE onboarding_documents SET
  html_content = '<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;"><img src="/logo.png" alt="The Lotus Program Experience" style="max-width:160px;height:auto;display:inline-block;" /></p><p style="text-align:center;color:#6B3A5E;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:24px;">The Lotus Program Experience</p><p><strong>Full Spectrum Doula Contract</strong></p><p>This agreement is entered into between _____________________________, hereafter referred to as the &quot;Client&quot;, and ___________________, hereafter referred to as the “Full Spectrum Doula” on this date: _____________________________.</p><p><strong>Definition of a Full Spectrum Doula:</strong> A Full Spectrum Doula is a trained professional who provides non-medical support to individuals and their families throughout the entire reproductive experience. This includes emotional, physical, and informational support before, during, and after childbirth, as well as during pregnancy loss, termination, or other reproductive health events. The goal of the Full Spectrum Doula is to support the client’s choices and needs with compassion, respect, and understanding, ensuring a positive experience regardless of the reproductive journey.</p><p>During the period of employment with the Client, the Full Spectrum Doula will be available by text or email during regular business hours when not physically present with the Client.</p><p><strong>Scope of Services:</strong> This contract outlines the services that the Full Spectrum Doula will provide to the client. The services are customized to each family''s needs, but can include:</p><ul><li><strong>Prenatal Support:</strong> Assistance with birth planning, including discussions about birth preferences, emotional support, and preparation for labor.</li><li><strong>Labor Support:</strong> Continuous physical, emotional, and informational support during labor, including comfort measures, relaxation techniques, and advocacy for the client’s birth preferences.</li><li><strong>Birth Coaching:</strong> Guidance on breathing, positioning, and movement to assist with the labor process, and emotional support throughout.</li><li><strong>Postpartum Support:</strong> Providing emotional support, postpartum recovery guidance, and assistance with newborn care, including initial breastfeeding support (if applicable).</li><li><strong>Reproductive Loss &amp; Termination Support:</strong> Providing emotional support, coping strategies, and resources for those experiencing pregnancy loss, miscarriage, or pregnancy termination.</li></ul><p>This agreement will begin on _________________ and end on ________________, unless otherwise agreed upon by both parties.</p><p><strong>Service Address:</strong> The Full Spectrum Doula will provide services at the Client''s home, birth center, hospital, or other agreed-upon location for the birth, as mutually determined.</p><p><strong>Rates and Payment Terms:</strong> The fee for services is based on an hourly or package rate, as agreed upon by both parties prior to the start of services. This will include a breakdown of services and fees outlined in this contract.</p><p>Our agreed-upon fee structure is as follows:</p><ul><li>$ ____.00 per hour for labor support (prenatal, birth, or postpartum).</li><li>$ ____.00 for prenatal consultation(s).</li><li>Additional support may be available for postpartum care or reproductive loss at an agreed-upon hourly rate.</li><li>The Full Spectrum Doula’s services will be available for _____ hours a day, ____ days per week, for _____ weeks, beginning __________, __<strong><em>, 202</em></strong>.</li></ul><p>Scheduled hours are from __________ to __________. Fees will be adjusted if there is an overlap into other hours (e.g., evening or early morning hours).</p><p>The client may request additional service hours upon agreement with the Full Spectrum Doula. The Full Spectrum Doula will do their best to meet the Client''s needs.</p><ul><li><strong>Payment is due prior to services being rendered.</strong></li><li><strong>Payment is accepted via Zelle, Venmo, PayPal, or through our website: ________________________.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Refund Policy:</strong> Fees are to be paid in full prior to services being rendered. These fees are not refundable.</p><p><strong>Additional Services that may require extra fees:</strong> If the Client requests services outside the Scope of Services, the Full Spectrum Doula will discuss any additional fees in advance.</p><p><strong>Fraudulent Chargebacks:</strong> The Full Spectrum Doula maintains a zero-tolerance policy toward fraudulent chargebacks and will fully pursue legal action. In the event of a legal dispute requiring court intervention, the Client agrees to cover all court expenses for both the Client and the Full Spectrum Doula.</p><p><strong>Cancellation and Rescheduling Policy:</strong> Clients must provide a 48-hour cancellation notice to the Full Spectrum Doula in writing. If the Client cancels without sufficient notice, the Client will be responsible for compensating the Full Spectrum Doula for the scheduled hours.</p><p>If the Full Spectrum Doula needs to cancel an appointment, they will provide as much notice as possible and will reschedule the appointment at a mutually convenient time.</p><p><strong>Limitations of the Full Spectrum Doula:</strong></p><ul><li>The Full Spectrum Doula does not perform medical tasks, such as blood pressure checks, fetal heart rate monitoring, vaginal exams, or any other medical procedures.</li><li>The Full Spectrum Doula does not provide medical advice, prescription medication information, or recommend dosages for medications.</li><li>The Full Spectrum Doula does not care for animals or pets in the client’s home. All animals must be securely housed during the provision of services.</li><li>The Full Spectrum Doula is not a nanny nor a housekeeper.</li></ul><p><strong>Disclosure of Communicable Diseases:</strong> The Client agrees to disclose any communicable diseases so that the Full Spectrum Doula can take appropriate precautions.</p><p><strong>Confidentiality:</strong> The Full Spectrum Doula agrees to maintain client confidentiality and will not disclose any information or details about the Client or their family to third parties without the Client''s express consent.</p><p><strong>Photography and Videography:</strong> This agreement permits the capturing of photos and videos during services for promotional purposes on the Full Spectrum Doula’s website, social media platforms, and marketing materials. The Full Spectrum Doula retains ownership of all photos and videos taken. The Client acknowledges that they do not possess any rights to the photos or videos taken by the Full Spectrum Doula.</p><p><strong>Liability:</strong> The Full Spectrum Doula is not liable for any unforeseen circumstances or events that may occur during the provision of services.</p><p><strong>Termination of Agreement:</strong> Either party may terminate this agreement by providing a 30-day written notice. All outstanding fees or charges owed to the Full Spectrum Doula must be paid in full before the termination of this agreement.</p><p>By signing below, the Client acknowledges that they have read and understood the terms and conditions of this agreement and agree to abide by them.</p><p><strong>Client Signature:</strong> ____________________________________</p><p><strong>Date:</strong> ___________________________</p><p><strong>Full Spectrum Doula Signature:</strong> _____________________________________</p><p><strong>Date:</strong> ____________________________</p>',
  has_fillable_fields = true,
  requires_doula_signature = false
WHERE slug = 'full-spectrum-contract';

UPDATE onboarding_documents SET
  html_content = '<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;"><img src="/logo.png" alt="The Lotus Program Experience" style="max-width:160px;height:auto;display:inline-block;" /></p><p style="text-align:center;color:#6B3A5E;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:24px;">The Lotus Program Experience</p><p><strong>Death Doula Contract</strong></p><p>This agreement is entered into between _____________________________, hereafter referred to as the &quot;Client&quot;, and ___________________, hereafter referred to as the “Death Doula,” on this date: _____________________________.</p><p><strong>Definition of a Death Doula:</strong><br />A Death Doula is a trained professional who provides non-medical emotional, spiritual, educational, and physical support to individuals and their loved ones during the dying process. The Death Doula offers compassionate presence and advocacy while helping to ensure that the client’s values, wishes, and dignity are honored throughout the final stages of life and into the early bereavement period.</p><p>During the term of this agreement, the Death Doula will be available by text or email during regular business hours when not physically present with the Client.</p><p><strong>Scope of Services:</strong><br />This contract outlines the services that the Death Doula will provide. Services may be customized based on the Client’s unique needs, beliefs, and priorities and may include:</p><p>• Emotional Support: Providing non-judgmental companionship, active listening, and reassurance to the Client and their support system.<br />• Vigil Planning: Assisting with creating a calm, sacred, and personalized environment during the dying process.<br />• Life Review &amp; Legacy Projects: Supporting the Client in reflecting on their life, sharing stories, or creating keepsakes or messages for loved ones.<br />• Support for Loved Ones: Offering guidance and presence to family and caregivers before, during, and after death.<br />• Non-Medical Comfort Measures: Helping create soothing environments using light, sound, scent, or touch (with consent).<br />• Rituals &amp; Ceremony: Assisting with meaningful end-of-life traditions or spiritual practices as desired by the Client.<br />• Grief &amp; Bereavement Support: Providing short-term support after death and referrals to counseling or support groups if needed.<br />• Advocacy &amp; Resources: Supporting communication with hospice teams or other professionals, and providing relevant educational materials.</p><p>This agreement will begin on _________________ and end on ________________, unless otherwise agreed upon by both parties.</p><p><strong>Service Location:</strong><br />Services may be provided virtually, in the Client’s home, or at another agreed-upon location such as a hospice facility, hospital, or care center.</p><p><strong>Rates and Payment Terms:</strong><br />Fees are based on an hourly rate or package rate, agreed upon prior to the start of services. All service packages and pricing will be outlined and mutually confirmed below:</p><p>• <strong>$____.00 per hour for end-of-life support (in-person, virtual, or emotional support).<br />• $____.00 </strong>for the initial consultation(s).<br />• Additional services such as extended vigil support, legacy project facilitation, or family meetings may be billed at a separate, agreed-upon rate.</p><p>The Death Doula will be available for _____ hours per day, _____ days per week, for a duration of _____ weeks, beginning on ________<strong>, 20__</strong>.</p><p>Scheduled support hours will be from __________ to __________, with adjustments made for early morning, evening, or overnight sessions, if needed and agreed upon.</p><p>• Payment is due prior to services being rendered.<br />• Accepted payment methods: Zelle, Venmo, PayPal, or via our website: ________________________</p><p><strong>Refund Policy:</strong><br />All payments are non-refundable. Services are reserved and scheduled in advance; your payment secures your time.</p><p><strong>Additional Services and Fees:</strong><br />If additional services are requested outside of the agreed scope, the Death Doula will provide a written estimate and receive client approval before proceeding.</p><p><strong>Fraudulent Chargebacks:</strong><br />The Death Doula maintains a zero-tolerance policy for fraudulent chargebacks and reserves the right to take legal action. The Client agrees to cover all legal and court costs in the event of a dispute requiring legal resolution.</p><p><strong>Cancellation &amp; Rescheduling Policy:</strong><br />Clients must provide at least 48 hours’ notice for cancellations. Missed appointments or cancellations without notice will be billed in full.</p><p>If the Death Doula must cancel a session, the Client will be notified promptly, and the session will be rescheduled at the earliest mutual convenience.</p><p><strong>Limitations of the Death Doula:</strong><br />• The Death Doula does not provide medical care, diagnosis, or clinical treatment.<br />• The Death Doula does not administer medications or offer medical advice.<br />• The Death Doula does not replace the care of a licensed therapist, psychologist, hospice provider, or physician.<br />• The Death Doula does not handle or transport human remains or provide funeral services.</p><p><strong>Health &amp; Safety:</strong><br />The Client agrees to disclose any known communicable diseases or health concerns to ensure proper precautions are taken.</p><p><strong>Confidentiality:</strong><br />All personal and medical information shared with the Death Doula will remain strictly confidential and will not be disclosed without the Client’s express written consent, except where required by law.</p><p><strong>Photography &amp; Videography (Optional Clause):</strong><br />With client consent, photos/videos taken during services (e.g., legacy work or rituals) may be used for promotional purposes, including website, marketing, or social media. All content remains the property of the Death Doula.</p><p>☐ I give permission for photos/videos to be used for promotional purposes.<br />☐ I do not give permission for any photos/videos to be used.</p><p><strong>Liability:</strong><br />The Death Doula is not liable for any medical or emotional outcomes. All support provided is non-medical and offered in a supportive, advisory capacity only.</p><p><strong>Termination of Agreement:</strong><br />Either party may terminate this agreement by providing written notice at least 30 days in advance. Any unpaid fees must be settled in full prior to termination.</p><p>By signing below, both parties acknowledge their understanding and acceptance of the terms outlined in this contract.</p><p><strong>Client Signature:</strong> ____________________________________<br /><strong>Date:</strong> ___________________________</p><p><strong>Death Doula Signature:</strong> ____________________________________<br /><strong>Date:</strong> ___________________________</p>',
  has_fillable_fields = true,
  requires_doula_signature = false
WHERE slug = 'death-doula-contract';

